{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HJ1PjBUV1nkJ64ZLAFDjbw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the current probe configuration:\n\n**Current probes (problematic):**\n- **Liveness probe:**\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 15` - too short for MongoDB with replica set initialization\n  - `periodSeconds: 15`\n  - `failureThreshold: 2` - very low, only 2 failures allowed\n  - `timeoutSeconds: 1` - very tight, mongosh connection can take longer\n\n- **Readiness probe:**\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 5` - way too short for startup\n  - `periodSeconds: 10`\n  - `failureThreshold: 2` - very low\n  - `timeoutSeconds: 1` - very tight\n\nThe core issues are that one-second timeouts are unrealistic for mongosh startup and authentication, the initial delays don't account for replica set initialization and keyfile auth overhead, and the failure threshold is too aggressive—with such tight timeouts, legitimate slowdowns trigger premature pod restarts.\n\nThe original configuration was much more reasonable: liveness probes waited 60 seconds before starting with 5-second timeouts and 10 failures allowed, while readiness probes gave 30 seconds with 5-second timeouts and 6 failures. I need to restore these values and then investigate the current pod state, mongod configuration, and replica set setup to understand what's actually failing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2269,"cache_read_input_tokens":28328,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2269},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4a98746-b82d-42e0-9fa6-7b08a3206e72","uuid":"f5cd82c8-9d05-4feb-8adc-9a63236ee310","request_id":"req_011CcfucZEsB1kQoMSj91tgW"}
